<subSubSection id="C33E6531CC54FFE3FF68C996FECFFA5F" box="[151,267,1508,1534]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC54FFE3FF68C996FECFFA5F" blockId="4.[151,606,1471,1534]" box="[151,267,1508,1534]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
(
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC54FFE3FF60C996FEC7FA5F" box="[159,259,1508,1534]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 3" captionStart-1="FIGURE 4" captionStartId-0="5.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionStartId-1="6.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox-0="[176,1436,186,1852]" captionTargetBox-1="[306,1281,741,1954]" captionTargetId-0="figure-17@5.[151,1436,181,1865]" captionTargetId-1="figure-349@6.[306,1281,741,1954]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="6" captionText-0="FIGURE 3. Calepitrimerus cryptocaryaer sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; AL, lateral view of anterior part of body; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; GM, male external genitalia; IG, female internal genitalia; LO, lateral microtubercles; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; PM, lateral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 27 μm for AL, PM; 15 μm for AD, CG, GM, IG, L1, L2; 5 μm for em, LO." captionText-1="FIGURE 4. Calepitrimerus cryptocaryaer sp. nov. A, dorsal view; B, prodorsal shield; C, female coxigenital area; D, female internal genitalia; E, male external genitalia. Scale bar: 20 μm for A; 10 μm for B, C, E; 5 μm for D." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524512" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524514" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6524512/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6524514/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Figs 3–4</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33E6531CC54FFE0FF68CA5EFDA6FD6C" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="286" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC54FFE3FF68CA5EFA4AF977" blockId="4.[151,1436,1580,2039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FF68CA5EFEBFF9E7" bold="true" box="[151,379,1580,1606]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Diagnosis (female).</emphasis>
Body fusiform; prodorsal shield with an acuminate frontal lobe, median line short, present at anterior 1/8 and posterior 1/8, admedian lines formed two large cells by transverse lines at center, admedian and submedian lines formed four large cells at each side, and many elliptical granules; legs with 4-rayed simple tarsal empodium, and knobbed tarsal solenidion; opisthosoma dorsally with elliptical microtubercles on ridges, while ventrally with elliptical to linear microtubercles; female genital coverflap with many dashes at base and 14 striae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC54FFE1FF38CA92FB1DFD6C" blockId="4.[151,1436,1580,2039]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,150,717]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="285" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FF38CA92FEDAF95B" bold="true" box="[199,286,1760,1786]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Female</emphasis>
(n = 8): Body fusiform (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC54FFE3FDD0CA92FD62F95B" box="[559,678,1760,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[306,1281,741,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-349@6.[306,1281,741,1954]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Calepitrimerus cryptocaryaer sp. nov. A, dorsal view; B, prodorsal shield; C, female coxigenital area; D, female internal genitalia; E, male external genitalia. Scale bar: 20 μm for A; 10 μm for B, C, E; 5 μm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524514/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Figure 4A</figureCitation>
), 182 (182–205) long, 63 (63–72) wide; light yellow in colour. Gnathosoma 17 (16–20) long, projecting obliquely downwards, cheliceral stylets 14 (14–18), pedipalp coxal seta (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FA87CB77FA56F8BF" box="[1400,1426,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">ep</emphasis>
) 3 (2–3), dorsal pedipalp genual setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FDB6CB5AFD93F8E3" box="[585,599,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">d</emphasis>
) 11 (11–12), palp tarsal ventral setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FBF2CB5BFBDDF8E3" box="[1037,1049,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">v</emphasis>
) absent. Prodorsal shield (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC54FFE3FAB9CB5AFF67F8C7" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[176,1436,186,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1436,181,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Calepitrimerus cryptocaryaer sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; AL, lateral view of anterior part of body; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; GM, male external genitalia; IG, female internal genitalia; LO, lateral microtubercles; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; PM, lateral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 27 μm for AL, PM; 15 μm for AD, CG, GM, IG, L1, L2; 5 μm for em, LO." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524512/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Figures 3</figureCitation>
AD, 4B) 53 (53–55), including the frontal lobe, 63 (63–75) wide, frontal lobe acuminate; median line short, present at anterior 1/8 and posterior 1/8, admedian lines formed two large cells by transverse lines at center, admedian and submedian lines formed four large cells at each side; many dashes present on prodorsal shield. Scapular tubercles ahead of rear shield margin, setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FDEDCBCBFDEDF873" box="[530,553,1977,2002]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">sc</emphasis>
5 (5–6), 21 (20–21) apart, projecting centrad. Coxigenital region with 6* semiannuli between coxae and genitalia, smooth; coxal plates (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC54FFE3FCDCCBAEFC48F857" box="[803,908,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[176,1436,186,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1436,181,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Calepitrimerus cryptocaryaer sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; AL, lateral view of anterior part of body; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; GM, male external genitalia; IG, female internal genitalia; LO, lateral microtubercles; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; PM, lateral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 27 μm for AL, PM; 15 μm for AD, CG, GM, IG, L1, L2; 5 μm for em, LO." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524512/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Figures 3</figureCitation>
CG, 4C) with granules, anterolateral setae on coxisternum І (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FEBECCE5FE99FF10" box="[321,349,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">1b</emphasis>
) 7 (6–7), 14 (13–15) apart; proximal setae on coxisternum І (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FBF7CCE5FBE1FF10" box="[1032,1061,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">1a</emphasis>
) 11 (10–11), 7 (7–8) apart; proximal setae on coxisternum ІІ (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FE1CCCC9FE3AFF74" box="[483,510,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">2a</emphasis>
) 25 (23–25), 25 (25–27) apart. Prosternal apodeme absent. Leg І (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC56FFE1FB10CCC9FAA1FF74" box="[1263,1381,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[176,1436,186,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1436,181,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Calepitrimerus cryptocaryaer sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; AL, lateral view of anterior part of body; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; GM, male external genitalia; IG, female internal genitalia; LO, lateral microtubercles; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; PM, lateral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 27 μm for AL, PM; 15 μm for AD, CG, GM, IG, L1, L2; 5 μm for em, LO." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524512/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">Figure 3L</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC56FFE1FA9ACCC9FAABFF74" box="[1381,1391,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1897,1921]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,569,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-230@2.[151,1436,561,1874]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Calepitrimerus liuanense sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; GM, male external genitalia; IG, female internal genitalia; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; DM, dorsal view of telosoma; VM, ventral view of telo- soma. Scale bar: 15 μm for AD, CG, DM, GM, IG, L1, L2, VM; 5 μm for em." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524508/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">1</figureCitation>
) 30 (30–33), femur 10 (9–10), basiventral femoral setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FD19CCADFCC4FF58" box="[742,768,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">bv</emphasis>
) 12 (10–12); genu 5*, antaxial genual setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FB09CCADFACEFF58" box="[1270,1290,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">l''</emphasis>
) 29 (29–30); tibia 8 (7–8), paraxial tibial setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FDEDCD71FDE4FEBC" box="[530,544,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">l'</emphasis>
) 5 (5–6), located at center; tarsus 5*, paraxial fastigial tarsal setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FB00CD71FAD1FEBC" box="[1279,1301,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">ft’</emphasis>
15 (15–19), antaxial fastigial tarsal setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FE1FCD55FE3BFEE0" box="[480,511,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">ft’’</emphasis>
22 (22–23), setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FD2BCD55FD2CFEE0" box="[724,744,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">u'</emphasis>
4 (4–5); tarsal empodium (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FBDDCD55FB87FEE1" box="[1058,1091,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">em</emphasis>
) 6 (6–7), simple, 4-rayed, tarsal solenidion (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FEBACD39FE9DFEC5" box="[325,345,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">ω</emphasis>
) 7*, knobbed. Leg ІІ (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC56FFE1FDA3CD39FD0BFEC4" box="[604,719,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[176,1436,186,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1436,181,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Calepitrimerus cryptocaryaer sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; AL, lateral view of anterior part of body; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; GM, male external genitalia; IG, female internal genitalia; LO, lateral microtubercles; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; PM, lateral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 27 μm for AL, PM; 15 μm for AD, CG, GM, IG, L1, L2; 5 μm for em, LO." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524512/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">Figure 3L</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC56FFE1FD30CD39FD19FEC4" box="[719,733,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,181,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[162,1425,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Calepitrimerus liuanense sp. nov. A, dorsal view of male; B, prodorsal shield; C, female coxigenital area; D, female internal genitalia; E, tarsus and empodium; F, male coxigenital area. Scale bar: 20 μm for A, D; 10 μm for B, C, F; 5 μm for D, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524510/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">2</figureCitation>
) 28 (28–30), femur 9 (8–9), basiventral femoral setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FAABCD39FAAAFEC4" box="[1364,1390,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">bv</emphasis>
) 10 (9–10); genu 4 (4–5), antaxial genual setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FD78CD1DFD5FFE28" box="[647,667,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">l''</emphasis>
) 5 (5–6); tibia 6*; tarsus 5*, paraxial fastigial tarsal setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FAD8CD1DFAF9FE28" box="[1319,1341,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">ft’</emphasis>
5 (5–6), antaxial fastigial tarsal setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FE28CDE1FE33FE0C" box="[471,503,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">ft’’</emphasis>
21 (19–21), setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FD3CCDE1FD13FE0C" box="[707,727,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">u'</emphasis>
4*; tarsal empodium (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FC2ECDE1FC36FE0D" box="[977,1010,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">em</emphasis>
) 6*, simple, 4-rayed, tarsal solenidion (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FF5ECDC5FF71FE71" box="[161,181,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">ω</emphasis>
) 6*, knobbed. Opisthosoma dorsally with 45 (43–45) semiannuli, with elliptical micotubercles on ridges, with three ridges, middorsal ridge ended on 26–27 annuli, in a broad furrow (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC56FFE1FC4DCDA9FBEEFE54" box="[946,1066,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[306,1281,741,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-349@6.[306,1281,741,1954]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Calepitrimerus cryptocaryaer sp. nov. A, dorsal view; B, prodorsal shield; C, female coxigenital area; D, female internal genitalia; E, male external genitalia. Scale bar: 20 μm for A; 10 μm for B, C, E; 5 μm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524514/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">Figure 4A</figureCitation>
); ventrally with 69 (69–71) semiannuli, with elliptical to linear microtubercles. Setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FD0FCD8DFCCFFDB8" box="[752,779,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">c2</emphasis>
19 (19–23), on ventral semiannulus 9*, 48 (48–50) apart; setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FF2ACE51FF27FD9C" box="[213,227,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">d</emphasis>
31 (28–31), on ventral semiannulus 24 (22–24), 25 (25–30) apart; setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FBFDCE51FBCAFD9D" box="[1026,1038,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">e</emphasis>
24 (24–30), on ventral semiannulus 43 (43–44), 11 (11–13) apart; setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FDD4CE35FDF7FDC0" box="[555,563,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">f</emphasis>
26 (22–26), 21 (21–24) apart, on 6th ventral semiannulus from rear; setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FA7FCE35FA58FDC0" box="[1408,1436,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">h1</emphasis>
5*, setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FEFFCE19FED9FD24" box="[256,285,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">h2</emphasis>
50 (48–53). Female genitalia (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC56FFE1FD89CE19FD1BFD24" box="[630,735,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[176,1436,186,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1436,181,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Calepitrimerus cryptocaryaer sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; AL, lateral view of anterior part of body; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; GM, male external genitalia; IG, female internal genitalia; LO, lateral microtubercles; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; PM, lateral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 27 μm for AL, PM; 15 μm for AD, CG, GM, IG, L1, L2; 5 μm for em, LO." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524512/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">Figures 3</figureCitation>
CG, 4C) 15 (15–16), 22* wide, coverflap with many dashes at base and 14 striae, setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC56FFE1FE4CCEFDFE0BFD08" box="[435,463,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">3a</emphasis>
15 (15–19), 13* apart. Internal genitalia (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC56FFE1FC51CEFDFBDEFD08" box="[942,1050,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[176,1436,186,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1436,181,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Calepitrimerus cryptocaryaer sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; AL, lateral view of anterior part of body; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; GM, male external genitalia; IG, female internal genitalia; LO, lateral microtubercles; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; PM, lateral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 27 μm for AL, PM; 15 μm for AD, CG, GM, IG, L1, L2; 5 μm for em, LO." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524512/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="285">Figures 3</figureCitation>
IG, 4D): spermathecae ovoid, oriented posterolaterad; spermathecal tubes relatively short; transverse genital apodeme trapezoidal.
</paragraph>
