</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC57FFE0FF38CF14FAC6FC20" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1113]" box="[199,1282,870,897]" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FF38CF14FE38FC20" bold="true" box="[199,508,870,897]" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Relation to the host plant.</emphasis>
Vagrant on lower leaf surface with no apparent symptom to the host.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33E6531CC57FFE0FF38CFF9FC4EFBF8" pageId="7" pageNumber="286" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC57FFE0FF38CFF9FD73FC68" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1113]" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FF38CFF9FE8AFC04" bold="true" box="[199,334,907,933]" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific designation 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC57FFE0FD89CFF9FCD1FC05" authorityName="Xue &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[630,789,907,932]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Calepitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cryptocaryaer">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FD89CFF9FCD1FC05" box="[630,789,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">cryptocaryaer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the generic name of host plant, 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC57FFE0FABACFF9FF13FC69" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Cryptocarya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FABACFF9FF13FC69" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Cryptocarya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, adding a postfix - 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FE55CFDDFE05FC69" box="[426,449,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">er</emphasis>
; masculine in gender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC57FFE0FF38CFA0FC4EFBF8" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1113]" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FF38CFA0FE0FFC4D" bold="true" box="[199,459,978,1004]" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Deferential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new specie is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC57FFE0FCE3CFA1FB7EFC4C" authority="Xue, Song &amp; Hong, 2006" authorityName="Xue, Song &amp; Hong" authorityYear="2006" box="[796,1210,979,1005]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Cryptocarya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fopingi">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FCE3CFA1FC49FC4C" box="[796,909,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">C. fopingi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B4BCC57FFE0FC69CFA1FB7EFC4C" author="Xue, X. - F. &amp; Song, Z. - W. &amp; Hong, X. - Y." box="[918,1210,979,1005]" pageId="7" pageNumber="286" pagination="31 - 41" refId="ref9175" refString="Xue, X. - F., Song, Z. - W. &amp; Hong, X. - Y. (2006) A new genus and three new species of Phyllocoptini (Acari: Eriophyidae: Phyllocoptinae) from the Qinling Mountains, Shaanxi Province, northwestern China. Zootaxa, 1275, 31 - 41. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1587.1.4" type="journal article" year="2006">Xue, Song &amp; Hong, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by prodorsal shield design, from 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC57FFE0FED3CF85FE1CFBB0" box="[300,472,1015,1041]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Lindera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glauca">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FED3CF85FE1CFBB0" box="[300,472,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Lindera glauca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC57FFE0FE18CF85FDA4FBB0" box="[487,608,1015,1041]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Lauraceae</taxonomicName>
), but can be differentiated by median line present at anterior and posterior 1/8 (median line continuous in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC57FFE0FE0AC869FDA1FB94" authorityName="Xue, Song &amp; Hong" authorityYear="2006" box="[501,613,1051,1077]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Cryptocarya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fopingi">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FE0AC869FDA1FB94" box="[501,613,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">C. fopingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), dorsal annuli with microtubercles on ridges (dorsal annuli smooth in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC57FFE0FA7CC869FF22FBF8" authorityName="Xue, Song &amp; Hong" authorityYear="2006" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Cryptocarya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fopingi">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FA7CC869FF22FBF8" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">C. fopingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and empodium 4-rayed (empodium 6-rayed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC57FFE0FCF5C84DFCBEFBF8" authorityName="Xue, Song &amp; Hong" authorityYear="2006" box="[778,890,1087,1113]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Cryptocarya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fopingi">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FCF5C84DFCBEFBF8" box="[778,890,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">C. fopingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
